      <p>These birds of prey inhabit nearly every terrain and climate, though they all prefer high, secluded nesting spots.</p>
      <p>A typical <a href="ch73s18.html#MonstersAnimals59">eagle</a> is about 3 feet long and has a wingspan of about 7 feet. The statistics presented here can describe any similar-sized, diurnal bird of prey.</p>
